{
  "doc_id": "58028",
  "text": "Ventralized ich embryos lack a ''shield'' (the zebrafish equivalent of the Spemann organizer) during gastrulation and do not express any of the genes characteristic for organizer formation [CITATION_1] . BMPactivity is also uniform across the ectoderm [CITATION_2] . As the mutation can be completely rescued by the introduction of ectopic b-catenin-2 mRNA, ich embryos provide an excellent paradigm to study the formation of the early organizer and to identify genes involved in this process. Using this experimental logic, previously we were able to discern the epistatic relationship between the Fgf-, Nodal-and BMP-signaling pathways [CITATION_3] .",
